title: For Sale:  100 rounds - 7.62x54 R - Russian/Polish/Bavarian/Bulgarian/Yugoslavian Surplus
postcontent:
Hello,


My name is Thomas Emard. Some of you Armslisters may have dealt with me regarding Mosin-Nagants or SKS rifles. I have started up my own ammunition company, Vexxer Munitions, and I decided to give my local Armslisters first grab at the ammunition. My selection is limited at the moment; I thought it better to keep a few types of ammunition in stock, rather than buy a bit of lots of types.

This ammunition is very solid. I won't say it's amazing, because let's face it, it's military surplus, and it's corrosive. But that being said, I've fired well over 100,000 rounds through my Mosin collection over the years, and I've had exactly 7 misfire or fail-to-feed.

Up for sale is 100 rounds, for $29. I have 17 in stock at the moment. A discount will be offered for bulk purchases. If you need some cheap ammunition for a shooting trip, or you're a prepper and you want to start stocking up on the world's most powerful surplus bullet, this ad is for you!


Contact me anytime with questions, and do make sure to check out my other ads. At the moment, all I'm offering for ammunition is 7.62x39mm and 7.62x54R, but I do have quite a few rifles and shotguns lying around for sale or trade.

I'd also like to take a moment and thank you personally, Armlister. You, and hundreds like you, have kept Portland's gun community strong. My first ad on here, I asked for Mosins. I was expecting a dozen, perhaps. I was stunned with the results; over the course of 4 weeks, two HUNDRED Mosins were offered for sale. So, thank you for using Armslist instead of your local gun dealer. The stronger the community becomes, the farther prices drop and the more selection we get. It is this fact that convinced me to post this ammunition for sale here, weeks in advance of my proper store being opened to the general American public.

As my business grows and I am able to place larger orders, the price will drop. Significantly. As it stands, I am making mere pennies on each order of 100 rounds, but I'd rather make tiny profit than have these rounds sitting around waiting for someone desperate enough to pay 'scalper' prices.


Regards,
Thomas

title: For Sale:  A weekend of shooting fun! August 9th
postcontent: Read this if you enjoy shooting guns!!  Only a few days left! Are you bored with the typical range session? Does standing still and shooting paper no longer interest you? We have the solution! A couple buddies and I sat down one day and decided to change the way we shoot.  We started up a club and named it RAC FRAG, or Responsible Armed Citizens, Fun Run And Gun. We set up a course that involves running from station to station and shooting the steel targets at various ranges. We transition from long range rifle targets to close range pistol targets, and back again.  Every gunner gets videoed and timed on their run so it puts a touch of stress into the mix. This course teaches you how to set up your gear, make quick mag changes, shoot while on the move, and shoot while shaking and out of breath. We found a fantastic piece of land near Madison Lake MN that we leased to hold our events. We had a good thunderstorm rip through the range at our last shoot but it didn't stop us from having fun.  Check out Rob's rainy run: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aAT8-rcd7pk.  We do other fun things out there besides running the course- like this example of me trying to be cool:  http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hC_zqy-FV9I   So come on out and join us for a ton of fun!  Our next big shoot is this Saturday, August 9th. Cost is $75 per person, or if you want to camp overnight with us and shoot some more on Sunday it's $120. We have a generator on site, a portable toilet, and a grill for whatever you want to bring to cook.  We are looking for more people to add to our club so if this sounds like something you might be interested in, respond to this ad or call/text me and lets chat! REDACTED Please let me know if you have any questions or if you want more info. Check out our website for more pics and videos: http://rac-frag.weebly.com/ Feel free to register on our home page for our August 9 shoot to hold your spot. If you register, you will also be placed on our mailing list for regular FRAG updates. Thanks!! Cody

title: For Sale:   FOR SALE: CAUTION! HUNTER MARTIN BAIT AND SWITCH ARTIST SELLING HERE!!!
postcontent:
I just had a very bad experience with a bait and switch liar here on Armslist. This excuse for a man goes by the name of "HUNTER MARTIN" I am not sure it is his real name but he uses google phone to hide his identity. He made off with a large sum of my hard earned cash and a very expensive Noveske Lower Receiver yesterday. He advertised a rifle where the internals did not match what was advertised or agreed upon through a series of text messages and in spoken word. As of now he is selling a Noveske KX3 pig for 300blk. He drives a brand new 2013 dark red Honda Civic and will ask to meet in a public place in the GRANTS PASS area. I suggest you do not do business with this THIEF!! 
Thank you

Pictures were found through his Google+ account. Photos must be 4+ years old..


EDIT: many people are asking more details of the transaction so here it is..


It was my first AR buy. My 4 year old and 8 month old came with me so it was a quick deal. It wasn't just the internals. 

The upper wasn't billet, the charging handle wasn't BCM and I didn't think to bring a measuring tape to check the gas length. He said the barrel was mid length gas, it was carbine. "Why are you selling this?"
I'd like to start my own mid-length AR build, and the money from this will go towards it.
"But it's the Sport version..."
Yup! That's exactly why I bought it -- I wanted to see if Smith put out a great rifle for the money, and they do! I was expecting it to not shoot nearly as well as my $1,000 Sig Sauer M400, but I was wrong. It's a great gun, especially for what you pay.

Yes, partially for these few AR components:
Geissele SSA or similar AR fire control group
B5 Systems/LMT sopmod stock
Bravo Company Gunfighter grips

Asking price: $640
Here is my breakdown:
M&P-15 Sport: $590 (I purchased this new for $675, and I have the original receipt if you’d like to see it. Because it is used, I'm taking off $85 in value)
All FDE Magpul Furniture: $50 (I purchased this new as well -- There is a handguard, MOE vertical grip, and medium rail section on the left high side)

Included is a black 30 Round PMAG, an enhanced rubber stock pad, the original box and manual it came with, as well as the original black plastic hand guards. The Aimpoint Red Dot you see in the pictures is not included (Unless you want to add another $430) – there is a Magpul rear BUIS included stock from the factory, which I’ve tested, and is zeroed for 50/200 yards with standard loads.

I’d prefer to meet at Scottsdale Gun Club, Shooter’s World (Phoenix), or, if need be, Cabela’s, to make the sale. You MUST show me a valid AZDL or CCW (I have both). Please keep in mind that just because this is a private sale does not mean a prohibited possessor can legally buy this rifle from me – Federal and State laws still apply. I will sign a bill of sale upon request; just bring it with when we meet up.

If you have any questions, please feel free to ask. All responses through this site will get e-mailed to my phone. I'm not some POS who is trying to rip you off, and as noted, feel that my asking price is fair; this said, if you want to make me a lower offer, I'll expect you to include some form of reasoning for why and how much that makes sense.

Thanks for your time!
